name: A romanian starry night
description:
Welcome to my page, here are some of my personal paintings done in oil on canvas.
size : 50x70cm
No .6
An interpretation after the Van Gogh's famous painting "Starry night".
This ain't an original painting, and is very different from what I did in the past, is more a warming up after half year pause.
I recently moved into a small remote village similar to the one in the painting, with old traditional houses, and the connection with the nature made everything be meaningful, such a different feeling from the one in the city, where I felt like a useless cog in a degrading, unconscious machine, everything culminating with the most frustrating period of my life, the quarantine, that was a breaking point of the hellish loop.
I never felt better, but very worried for the direction the world is going into...
